.sp 1
Write a core file if the program dies\&. The name and location of the core file are system\-dependent\&. (For MySQL Cluster programs nodes running on Linux, the default location is the program\'s working directory\(emfor a data node, this is the node\'s
DataDir\&.) For some systems, there may be restrictions or limitations; for example, it might be necessary to execute
\fBulimit \-c unlimited\fR
before starting the server\&. Consult your system documentation for detailed information\&.
.sp
If MySQL Cluster was built using the
\fB\-\-debug\fR
option for
\fBconfigure\fR, then
\fB\-\-core\-file\fR
is enabled by default\&. For regular builds,
\fB\-\-core\-file\fR
is disabled by default\&.
.RE
